<TITLE> Dhaka-Ctg rail link restored after 8h break </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Feni, Mar 1 (bdnews24.com)  Rail communication between Dhaka and Chittagong was restored after an eight hour break due to a derailment on Monday. The communication restored at around 11am, said Matiur Rahman, senior deputy assistant engineer of Bangladesh Railway (east zone). Several trains remained stranded at railway stations along the route after two carriages of a Dhaka bound freight train went off the tracks near Feni's Fazilpur station at around 3.00am, he said. A salvage train went to the spot from Chittagong and rescued the carriages, Matiur said. There were no casualties, the official added. bd
